Realm Report is a closed-source project. This repository publishes only the
addon's documentation and screenshots. The source code is intentionally not
made public.


Why this project is closed source
---------------------------------
Realm Report shows live WvW objective state by reading the Guild Wars 2
client's memory, which relies on reverse engineering of the game client.
Publishing the source would also publish those reverse-engineering details, so
the code is kept private.

Realm Report only reads the game's memory; it never writes to or modifies the
game's memory or code. The only action it performs on your behalf — copying an
objective's nearest waypoint chat link to your clipboard, which you paste
yourself — simply reproduces something you could already do by hand. Realm
Report does not alter game state directly, inject code into the game, bot, or
automate gameplay.


Permitted use
-------------
You may download and use the Realm Report addon free of charge, including while
streaming, recording, or making videos or other content — on monetised channels
as well as personal ones. Streamers and content creators are warmly welcome to
feature and showcase Realm Report. You may also quote or reuse this
repository's documentation and screenshots when describing, reviewing, or
showcasing Realm Report, with attribution.

This permission does not let you sell Realm Report, charge others for access to
it, or bundle it into a paid product or service — see Restrictions below.


Distribution via Raidcore / Nexus
---------------------------------
The author grants Raidcore and the Nexus addon library (raidcore.gg) permission
to list, host, and distribute the Realm Report addon, unmodified and free of
